FBIS3-30707 "dreeu026__a94079" FBIS-EEU-94-026-A Document Type:Daily Report 8 February 1994 ANNEX Slovakia Poll Shows HZDS Leading; Kovac Most Trusted AU0702112394 Prague CTK in English 1133 GMT 5 Feb 94 AU0702112394 Prague CTK Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Bratislava, February 5 (CTK) -- Seventeen percent of Slovaks support Premier Vladimir Meciar's Movement For a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), while 14 percent support the Democratic Left Party (SDL) and just over 7 percent the Christian Democratic Movement (KDH), according to a poll by the Focus agency whose results were broadcast by Slovak radio today. President Michal Kovac emerged as the most trustworthy politician (25 percent). Next came Vladimir Meciar with 21 percent and third SDL Chairman Peter Weiss with 14 percent. The poll was conducted between January 26 and February 1, and therefore its results were not influenced by the present political crisis in the Slovak parliament, the radio warned.
